      • getContents

        public retrofit2.Call<Contents> getContents(retrofit2.Callback<Contents> callback)

        Asynchronously send the contents request and notify callback.

        Note: If response code is 404 or 500, you can parse error message using ErrorUtils.parseError(retrofit2.Response<?>).

        For example: 
         LeantegraCmsClient client = new LeantegraCmsClient();
  ...
  client.getContents(new Callback<Contents>() {
      @Override
      public void onResponse(Call<Contents> call, Response<Contents> response) {
          if (!response.isSuccessful()) {
              APIError error = ErrorUtils.parseError(response);
          }else{
              Contents contents = response.body();
              //Use contents
              ...
          }
      }

      @Override
      public void onFailure(Call<Contents> call, Throwable throwable) {
          //Handle error
      }
  });
        Parameters:
        callback - Response callback
        Returns:
        Call<Contents> object through which you can cancel request or get status
        Since:
        1.1.0
